body:
Scalafmt currently formats function application like this
```scala
// 40 columns                          |
object FunctionApplication {
  // 1. Fits on a single line
  function(arg1, arg2, arg3)

  // 2. Fits on a single line, with newline indented by 4
  function(
      longerArg1, longerArg2, arg3)

  // 3. One line for each argument, indented at (
  function(longerArg1,
           longerArg2,
           longerArg3)

  // 4. One line for each argument, indented at 4
  function(
      superDuperLongArg(
          evenHasNestedArgs,
          notOnlyOneButTwo), // This arg is too long.
      arg2IsNotAsBad)

}
```

I propose to eliminate the second option. I've come across several diffs where the second option produces quite bad output. Examples
```scala
// Original
-    val dataSourceResult = 
-      FastEvalEngineWorkflow.getDataSourceResult(
-        workflow = workflow,
-        prefix = new DataSourcePrefix(prefix))
// current
+    val dataSourceResult = FastEvalEngineWorkflow.getDataSourceResult(
+        workflow = workflow, prefix = new DataSourcePrefix(prefix))
// proposed
+    val dataSourceResult = FastEvalEngineWorkflow.getDataSourceResult(
         workflow = workflow,
         prefix = new DataSourcePrefix(prefix))
// Original
-  def batchPredictBase(sc: SparkContext, bm: Any, qs: RDD[(Long, Q)])
-  : RDD[(Long, P)]
// Current
+  def batchPredictBase(
+      sc: SparkContext, bm: Any, qs: RDD[(Long, Q)]): RDD[(Long, P)]
// Proposed
+  def batchPredictBase(sc: SparkContext,
                        bm: Any,
                        qs: RDD[(Long, Q)]): RDD[(Long, P)]
```

I understand this would come at the cost of vertical space in cases where there are many but small arguments. From best what I can tell, rustfmt and clang-format don't have rule 2 or 4. Dartfmt does have option 2 but otherwiseÂ [uses quite different rules from scalafmt (see section Rules)](http://journal.stuffwithstuff.com/2015/09/08/the-hardest-program-ive-ever-written/).

A nice side-effect, the search space is smaller which makes formatting faster ^^
